				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have both a Beastlord (4  and a Mage (53 and 60). Last thread I saw completely degraded into flames. I want to set some facts straight.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Mage pets - Mage pets are their class. Pre 50, Mage pets are about as powerful as a Beastlord pet, except Beastlord's get their pets at a slower rate (9, 15, 22, 30, 39, 49) than Mages (4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 30, 34, 39, 44, 49). 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Mage spells vs pets - Mage heals and pet buffs are very weak compared to Beastlord ones. Our best heal pre pop has a 2.25 Mana to Damage ratio. Mages only get 5 Haste spells, at 20, 39, 49, 56, and 60/63 (Ancient one at 60 is same as 63 one). We get no procs/other buffs. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Mage nukes - Mage nukes are situational. Unlike all other casters, we suffer from having no low-resist nukes. This means that in situations with Lure only/Bad resist mobs, Mages only get damage from Damage Shields and Pets. However, we can do a ton of damage vs low resist mobs.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Mage epic - The Mage epic is, by far, the hardest epic in the game. It requires you do get a Piece from the 7th isle of PoA, A piece which is Phinny's rarest drop, And a piece from a rare Hate-Mini-Boss. Not to mention the rare drop cloak off Quillmane in South Karana. Like Quillmane, we have 6 other Greenie-rare drop mobs we have to camp for hours on end.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Beastlord Balance - Beastlords need their melee upgraded. Their pets are fine, and scale up with PoP. However, your melee does not improve too much. I don't think Double Attack would be overpowering(not the AA).
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Mages really aren't overpowered. Mages will do 100-120 DPS on some fights, and 40 DPS on others. Beastlords are just underpowered. "History is just a set of lies agreed upon" - Emperor Napoleon Bonaparte
<br />
<i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
