			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Mage and Beastlords are very different. Both classes rely on there pets alot. However that is where the similarities end. When it comes to engaging a mob 1 on 1 a mage and beastlord hand things completely differently. Even now the mage epic pet is still very good, and has higher dps then all of the pets in the game except the new mage water pet. Against lvl 60 and lower debuffed mob most all pets will have a hard time keeping up. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
The argument that beastlords can buff there pets better then mages. Well it depends on what you are talking about. A mage can give his pet focus gear which if I remember correctly has AC8 on each piece. Also a mage can give his pet a full suit of plate mail and give it a permanent hp increase of up to almost 800hps and about 50 or 60 ac not including the ac bonus that burnout 5 gives. Also the new post 60 belts have stats. So even tho a beastlord can give his pet more stats buffs then a mage. He can't give his pets more ac/hps then a mage can give his pet. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Beastlords can imbue their pets with different procs. Well mages can do that now to. We can give our pet two different types of procs at the same time, one in each hand procing for 160dd. Mage pets cast spells as well. The new water pet's dd spell is higher damage then the beastlord procs and on top of that we can give the pet procing weapons. All these &quot;buffs&quot; are mana free to the mage once we give them to the pets while the beastlord much keep refreshing his buffs on the pet.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
From the parsing I have done, it appears that the level 62 beastlord pet is very nice, and is very close to the lvl 61 air pet but still inferior. The level 64 beastlord pet seems to be possibly a little more damaging then the lvl 61 air pet but doesn't mitigate damage as well. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
All in All the classes are pretty much balanced now. Beastlord Pets are still weaker then mage pets but not by as much as they were before. To compensate for that mages have been given huge offensive upgrades in nuking.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
I am very happy for beastlords. I have a lvl 34 beastlord myself, as well as a 65 mage. I am looking forward to leveling him up now that alot of the problems the beastlord class had has been fixed. Mages offensively are still ahead of beastlords in sustained dps, while beastlords have moved closer to monks in dps. I think things are pretty well balanced, and more threads that try to put two classes against each other is getting old.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Wezloc 
<br />

<br />
65 Arch Convoker
<br />

<br />
Master of the Orb <i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
