				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I can't speak for the high end game, but let me tell you a little story about something that happened to me when I was level 20. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
I was in High Keep, in a WR group, killing goblins (god, it's sooo boring)/. The mage in the group kept going on about how inferior bst pets were to mage pets. I didn't say much,just kept playing. One funny thing was how they were looting. Whoever got the kill, got to loot. Well, lil Frite (my gator) got about 80% of the kills, I was making some good coin!
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Anyway, just before I left, I asked Mr. Mage (who was level 28, not sure what level they get their new pets) if he would like for our pets to duel. I still had my level 15 pet, and he was fully buffed (just by me). 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Frite tore his air elemental apart. I don't know if he was trying to heal his pet, or if he was nuking my gator, but something pissed Frite off. Frite turned on him, with the Air Elemental wailing on his back. He actually made a nice dent in the mage, before turning back on the Air Elemental. The two pets engaged in battle once again, and shortly thereafter the Air Elemental died. Frite still had about a bubble of HP left.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Needless to say, I was very impressed. 
<br />

