			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Having played my beastlord now to 57, and a magi to 55, I do have a bit of authority on how the classes compare. Magi can outdamage of course, and yes both can solo... With full raid buffs you can take on a lot of stuff that normally you couldnt, so dont even compare it to those everyday situations where you would probably be self buffed with a KEI on top of it should you choose to hunt that way. 
<br />

<br />
Magi pets are better at damage dealin, no doubt about it, they tank a bit better. Magi themselves can do a lot of damage with nukes, no doubt about that either. 
<br />

<br />
However, a magi cant slow a mob, a magi cant cast sow to aggro kite (though run three alleviates this slightly), a magi cant efficiently heal a mob without reducing their DPS (through lack of nuking). Beastlords are by far better soloers, at almost all levels Ive played to so far. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
You say you can take red mobs? sure, if you keep aggro off of pet you can and it doesnt summon, you just kite the thing around on your bum with a sowed pet (magi or beastlord, effect is the same) with taunt off, hoping you dont get lag.. I do it from time to time when there isnt a group going. 
<br />

<br />
Well, magi can solo, but they work best in pairs with another class, chanters are good, shamans particularly good. But join up with your beastlord friends, and use the combination of minor slows, pet heals and damage shields to your advantage.. Why solo when together you can conquer? and no, with the advent of PoP soloing is NOT more efficient, for virtually any class. 
<br />

<br />
Merry Christmas to you all, and team up with a magi!
<br />

<br />
 <i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
